# Parallel Task Execution

## Rule
Always launch independent tasks in parallel. Never run sequentially what can run concurrently.

## When dispatching agents
- If 2+ tasks have no data dependencies, launch them in a SINGLE message with multiple Agent tool calls
- Before dispatching, explicitly identify which tasks depend on each other and which are independent
- Group: independent tasks → parallel batch, then dependent tasks → next batch

## When running shell commands
- If 2+ commands are independent (e.g. lint + typecheck + test on different packages), run them as parallel Bash calls in one message
- Only chain with `&&` when commands are truly sequential

## When reading/searching files
- If you need to read 2+ files, issue all Read calls in one message
- If you need to search for 2+ patterns, issue all Grep/Glob calls in one message

## Anti-patterns (never do these)
- Running agent A, waiting for result, then running independent agent B
- Reading file A, waiting, then reading unrelated file B
- Running `make lint` then `make typecheck` sequentially when they don't depend on each other

## Think in dependency graphs
Before any multi-step work, mentally construct:
```
Task A (independent) ─┐
Task B (independent) ─┤── parallel batch 1
Task C (independent) ─┘
         │
Task D (needs A+B) ───── batch 2
         │
Task E (needs D) ─────── batch 3
```
